# Title (max. 50 characters)
# Summarize the changes concisely using the imperative mood.
# Format: <type>: <subject>
# Example: fix: fix login issue

# Message Body (max. 72 characters per line)
# Explain *what* was changed and *why* (not how).
# Separate paragraphs with a blank line.

# Example:
#
# Fix issue in the user login flow
# by adjusting the authentication logic. The previous method
# did not comply with the new security requirements.
#
# - Use bullet points to list changes
# - Prefer "-" or "*", followed by a space
# - Leave a blank line between idea groups

# Related issue (optional)
# Closes #123

# Special Note (optional)
# Example:
# - Run `rake db:migrate`
# - Check token in environment variables

# Co-authorship (optional)
# Co-authored-by: Full Name <email@example.com>

# Recommended title types:
# feat: New feature
# fix: Bug fix
# refactor: Code refactoring
# style: Formatting changes without affecting logic
# docs: Documentation updates
# test: Add or improve tests
# chore: General maintenance or auxiliary tasks
# perf: Performance improvement
# ci: Continuous integration configuration
# build: Build process or dependency changes
# revert: Revert a previous commit
# wip: Work in progress
# hack: Temporary workaround; avoid if possible
